==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Middle English]] ''[[awaken]]'', from [[Old English]] ''[[awacan]]'', from ''[[a-]]'' (intensive prefix) + ''[[wacan]]'' (wake).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ə'weɪk/}}
* {{audio|en-us-awake.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪk|-eɪk]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}
# not [[asleep]]; [[conscious]].
# {{vulgar}} acquainted with, knowing the business.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|awakes|awaking|'''[[awoke]]''' ''or'' '''[[awaked]]'''|'''[[awoken]]''' ''or'' '''[[awaked]]'''}}
# {{intransitive}} to become [[conscious]] after having [[sleep|slept]].
# {{transitive}} to cause somebody to stop [[sleep|sleeping]].
# {{transitive}} to [[excite]] or to [[stir up]] something [[latent]].

